$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Mu kubala ne kompyuta, hexadecimal (nayo base 16, oba hex) nkola ya namba ey’ekifo nga erina radix, oba base, ya 16. Ekozesa obubonero kkumi na mukaaga obw’enjawulo, emirundi mingi obubonero 0–9 okukiikirira emiwendo gya ziro okutuuka ku mwenda, . ne A, B, C, D, E, F (oba mu ngeri endala a–f) okukiikirira emiwendo kkumi okutuuka ku kkumi n’etaano. Okugeza, namba ya hexadecimal 2AF3 yenkana, mu decimal, ne (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , oba 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Buli digito ya hexadecimal ekiikirira digito nnya eza binary (bits) (era eziyitibwa &quot;nibble&quot;), era enkozesa enkulu ey&#39;ennyiriri za hexadecimal eri nga okukiikirira okw&#39;omukwano eri abantu okw&#39;emiwendo egy&#39;enkoodi bbiri mu kompyuta n&#39;ebyuma bya digito. Okugeza, emiwendo gya byte giyinza okuva ku 0 okutuuka ku 255 (decimal) naye giyinza okulagibwa mu ngeri ennyangu nga digito bbiri eza hexadecimal mu bbanga 00 okutuuka ku FF. Hexadecimal era etera okukozesebwa okukiikirira endagiriro z’ekijjukizo kya kompyuta.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex kifupi kya Hexadecimal, nga kino kyesigamiziddwa ku nsengekera ya base -16 era nga kikozesebwa okwanguyiza engeri ebiragiro eri kompyuta gye bikiikirira. Enkola eno ey’ennamba z’obubonero 16 yakolebwa ng’engeri y’okuziyiza ennamba ya binary eya bit 8, kale data esobola okuteekebwa mu kompyuta awatali kufuba kwonna. Kiyinza okuwandiikibwa n’okuwandiikibwa nga tukozesa digito za hex bbiri ez’enjawulo nga buli digito ya hex eraga nibble oba mpozzi ensengeka ya 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Enkola eno ey’ennamba ekozesa obubonero 16 obulagibwa mu bbanga okuva ku 0-9 oba AF. 0–9 zikiikirira namba okutuuka ku mwenda so nga AF ekiikirira namba 10–15. Bw’ogeraageranya n’ebika ebirala ebisatu eby’ensengekera z’ennamba, enkola y’ennamba eya hexadecimal etwalibwa ng’esinga okukola obulungi.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Koodi yo eya hexadecimal si ntuufu';
